00:41:56.350 --> 00:42:01.180
So these two fields have a
projector on the full theory

00:42:01.180 --> 00:42:10.546
field, and they obey n bar
slash, n slash, n slash,

00:42:10.546 --> 00:42:11.440
n bar slash.

00:42:11.440 --> 00:42:13.266
Cn is Cn.

00:42:13.266 --> 00:42:21.430
And the n bar slash n
slash by n bar is by n bar.

00:42:21.430 --> 00:42:23.800
So I want to write out the
QCD Lagrangian in terms

00:42:23.800 --> 00:42:26.223
of component because the
different derivatives,

00:42:26.223 --> 00:42:28.390
the different components
of the covariant derivative

00:42:28.390 --> 00:42:30.760
and the different
regular derivatives

00:42:30.760 --> 00:42:35.620
inside that derivative, have
different power counting, OK?

00:42:35.620 --> 00:42:37.210
So let's do that.

00:42:37.210 --> 00:42:39.550
And I'll introduce these two
fields in order to do that.

00:42:42.280 --> 00:42:47.020
So if you like, I'm just taking
QCD and writing it in these

00:42:47.020 --> 00:42:49.842
coordinates that we're
setting our usual coordinates

00:42:49.842 --> 00:42:50.800
