00:47:06.330 --> 00:47:09.090
And, therefore, I don't need
to have any current in my path

00:47:09.090 --> 00:47:10.920
integral that I
couple to this guy.

00:47:31.990 --> 00:47:33.970
So it's like an auxiliary
field if you like.

00:47:38.980 --> 00:47:41.530
And because the path integral
in this fermionic field

00:47:41.530 --> 00:47:44.200
is quadratic, we can just
remove it from the path,

00:47:44.200 --> 00:47:45.730
just do the path
integral over it.

00:47:48.770 --> 00:47:50.770
Once we know that there's
