00:47:50.770 --> 00:47:54.280
we can just do the path
integral since all the terms are

00:47:54.280 --> 00:47:55.560
explicitly written over there.

00:48:04.730 --> 00:48:07.880
So let's see what
happens when we do that.

00:48:07.880 --> 00:48:10.750
So doing the path integral
for this quadratic field just

00:48:10.750 --> 00:48:12.640
means solving the
equations of motion.

00:48:21.200 --> 00:48:24.970
So we take the variational
derivative with respect

00:48:24.970 --> 00:48:27.717
to phi n bar of the Lagrangian.

00:48:27.717 --> 00:48:29.425
And that gives us the
following equation.

00:48:57.030 --> 00:49:01.740
We could multiply both
terms in this equation

00:49:01.740 --> 00:49:05.160
by an n bar slash over 2.

00:49:05.160 --> 00:49:08.340
And then we can use the
projection relation.

00:49:08.340 --> 00:49:10.487
Just to simplify the
Dirac structure a little,

00:49:10.487 --> 00:49:12.570
we can move the Dirac
structure from here to here.

00:49:34.920 --> 00:49:37.440
And then we could formally solve
this equation for the phi n

00:49:37.440 --> 00:49:37.940
bar.

00:49:42.080 --> 00:49:44.374
It's an inverse
covariant derivative.

00:49:50.675 --> 00:49:52.947
I can push this through
this at the cost of a sign.

00:49:52.947 --> 00:49:54.530
So if I move it to
the right-hand side

00:49:54.530 --> 00:49:58.850
of the equation, that
takes care of that sign.

00:49:58.850 --> 00:50:00.768
So I did two sign changes.

00:50:00.768 --> 00:50:02.060
I moved something to the right.

00:50:02.060 --> 00:50:04.790
And then I pushed these
through each other

00:50:04.790 --> 00:50:07.570
to get that equation.

00:50:07.570 --> 00:50:08.070
OK.

00:50:08.070 --> 00:50:21.696
So what this is saying, in
terms of the original field,

00:50:21.696 --> 00:50:23.570
is that I have this
equation for psi.

00:50:27.450 --> 00:50:30.630
So if we take that
result and we plug it

00:50:30.630 --> 00:50:43.720
back into our Lagrangian,
which I meant to give a star,

00:50:43.720 --> 00:50:50.650
then we'll just have an
equation in terms of the C.

00:50:50.650 --> 00:50:53.080
We already used two terms.

00:50:53.080 --> 00:50:55.300
And so those two terms,
